<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/724> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #724" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.38.8; Diod. 16.82.1; Dion. Hal. 15.3.1; Chr. 354 (Hala III et Rutillo IIII); Fast. Hyd. (Achala et Rutilio II); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 106, 408f. While Servilius remained in Rome (Liv. 7.38.8), Marcius in Campania broke up a Roman conspiracy to seize Campanian territory (Liv. 7.38.8-39; Dion. Hal. 15.3; Frontin. Str. 1.9.1, A. Manlius; App. Samn. 1, {Gr}). On the resulting mutiny, see Dictator and Tribunes of the Plebs." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/723> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #723" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Servilius, see Fast. Cap. on 365; on that of Marcius, see Act. Tr. on 356 and 357. Diod. has {Gr}." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/685> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #685" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.22.11. See Degrassi 105, 404f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/684> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #684" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the names of Fabius and Servilius, see Act. Tr. on 360 and Fast. Cap. on 365. Cf. Val. Max. 2.7.8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/663> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #663" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "After long delay two patrician Consuls were elected (Liv. 7.17.10-12, and 18.1). Servilius and M. Fabius were appointed twice (Liv.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/641> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #641" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Rei gerundae causa, Liv. 7.11.4; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Ahala); Degrassi 34f., 105, 400f. Defeated Gallic forces near the Colline gate (Liv. 7.11.5-7 and 9)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/640> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #640" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Servilius' name, see Fast. Cap. on 365. On that of Quinctius, see 361, note 2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/623> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #623" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.4.1, and 6.12; Diod. 16.4.1; Fast. Cap. ([- - - -] Ahala II; G.'s name entire); Chr. 354 (Haala II et Abentinense); Fast. Hyd. (Achala et Genucio); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 104, 400f. Genucius was killed in battle with the Hernici (Liv. 7.6.7-9)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/622> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #622" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "In Diod. Genucius also has the praenomen Quintus. In Fast. Cap. no note was added regarding the death of Genucius. See Fast. Cap. for 365, which supplements the names as given here." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/612> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #612" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 7.1.7; Diod. 15.90.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -Ave]ntinensis; S.'s name entire); Eutrop. 2.4; Chr. 354 (Abentinensis et Haala); Oros. 3.4.1; Cassiod.; Lyd. Magg. 1.46. See Degrassi 32f., 104, 400f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/611> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #611" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Genucius, see Fast. Cap. for 362. On Fast. Hyd. and Chr. Pasc., see 366, note 1." .
